Vestel Beyaz Esya Sanayi & Ticaret
AS, a Turkish household appliances maker owned by Zorlu Holding
AS, rose the most in more than a year after Hurriyet reported
the company bought four brands from  Italy â€™s Antonio Merloni SpA.  The shares surged 21 kurus, or 10 percent, to 2.28 liras at
10:35 a.m., the biggest gain since May 2010 on a closing basis.  Vestel bought the Servis, Electra, Atlantic and New Pool
home appliance brands from Merloni and plans to raise annual
exports to $1 billion within three years from a forecast $750
million this year, Hurriyet newspaper said, citing Vestel Deputy
